modules.description: This module provides functions to interact with an InfluxDB server, specifically supporting ping and write operations. It works with InfluxDB hosts, databases, and time series data points, using asynchronous deferred responses for handling I/O. Concrete use cases include sending a health check to an InfluxDB instance and writing batches of time series data to a specified database.

This module enables interaction with an InfluxDB server through asynchronous operations, supporting health checks and writing time series data. It handles hosts, databases, and data points, using deferred responses for I/O. You can ping an InfluxDB instance to verify connectivity or write batches of timestamped metrics to a database. For example, it allows sending a health check request or logging system metrics at regular intervals.
